        <div class="intro-inner">
            <div class="journal-badge">Journal of Professional Excellence</div>
            <div class="intro-title">Loading Manuscript...</div>
            <div class="progress-track">
                <div class="progress-bar" id="progressBar"></div>
            </div>
            <div class="progress-label" id="progressLabel">Peer Review Status: Under Review...</div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- MAIN CONTENT -->
    <main class="paper" id="paper">
        <div class="lab-narrative">
            <h1 class="paper-title">A STUDY IN APPLIED INTELLIGENCE</h1>
            <div class="paper-meta">d'agnelli, d. (2012-present) | london, uk</div>
            <div class="paper-section">
                <h2>ABSTRACT</h2>
                <p>this paper presents the career trajectory of a practitioner operating at the intersection of artificial intelligence, machine learning, and enterprise programme management. the subject demonstrates sustained competency across supervised and unsupervised learning, deep neural networks, reinforcement learning, and large language models, while simultaneously directing programmes exceeding $15m in value.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="paper-section">
                <h2>KEY FINDINGS</h2>
                <p>the subject completed stanford machine learning (2016), followed by deeplearning.ai neural networks, udacity deep learning and deep reinforcement learning nanodegrees, and imperial college mathematics for ml. stanford probabilistic graphical models completed with honors. recent work includes genai rag systems deployment at enterprise scale.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="paper-section">
                <h2>METHODOLOGY</h2>
                <p>primary toolkit: python, java, go, rust. infrastructure: aws/azure/gcp, mlops, gitops. experimental design: agile & waterfall hybrid. sample sizes: 100+ plants, 2,000+ end users, 75k-employee organisations.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="paper-section">
                <h2>CONCLUSION</h2>
                <p>the evidence supports classification as a full-spectrum ai practitioner who chose the management track. gchq-certified msc in ethical hacking (distinction) noted as anomalous but consistent with subject's pattern of relentless acquisition.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="correspondence">CORRESPONDENCE: <a href="mailto:daniele@dagnelli.net">daniele@dagnelli.net</a></div>
        </div>
    </main>
</body>
</html>

<style>
    /* =========================================
       BASE & CUSTOM PROPERTIES
       ========================================= */
    * { box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0; padding: 0; }

    html {
        --lab-white: #ffffff;
        --lab-blue: #1a5276;
        --graph-red: #c0392b;
        --annotation-green: #27ae60;
        --paper-gray: #f8f9fa;
        --border: #dee2e6;
        --text-primary: #212529;
        --text-secondary: #495057;
        --text-muted: #6c757d;
        --serif: 'Source Serif 4', 'Georgia', serif;
        --mono: 'Fira Code', 'Courier New', monospace;
        --sans: 'Inter', -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, sans-serif;
    }

    body {
        background: var(--lab-white);
        color: var(--text-primary);
        font-family: var(--serif);
        font-size: 16px;
        line-height: 1.8;
        overflow: hidden;
        height: 100dvh;
    }

    a { color: var(--lab-blue); text-decoration: none; }
    a:hover { color: var(--graph-red); text-decoration: underline; }

    ::selection { background: rgba(26, 82, 118, 0.2); color: var(--text-primary); }

    /* =========================================
       GRID PAPER OVERLAY
       ========================================= */
    .grid-overlay {
        position: fixed;
        inset: 0;
        z-index: 0;
        pointer-events: none;
        background-image:
            linear-gradient(rgba(26, 82, 118, 0.03) 1px, transparent 1px),
            linear-gradient(90deg, rgba(26, 82, 118, 0.03) 1px, transparent 1px);
        background-size: 20px 20px;
    }

    /* =========================================
       INTRO SEQUENCE
       ========================================= */
    .intro {
        position: fixed;
        inset: 0;
        z-index: 10001;
        background: var(--lab-white);
        display: flex;
        align-items: center;
        justify-content: center;
        padding: 2rem;
        transition: opacity 0.4s ease;
    }
    .intro.done {
        opacity: 0;
        pointer-events: none;
    }
    .intro-inner {
        text-align: center;
        max-width: 480px;
        width: 100%;
    }
    .journal-badge {
        font-family: var(--sans);
        font-size: 11px;
        font-weight: 600;
        text-transform: uppercase;
        letter-spacing: 3px;
        color: var(--lab-blue);
        border: 2px solid var(--lab-blue);
        display: inline-block;
        padding: 6px 18px;
        margin-bottom: 28px;
    }
    .intro-title {
        font-family: var(--serif);
        font-size: 18px;
        color: var(--text-secondary);
        margin-bottom: 24px;
        font-style: italic;
    }
    .progress-track {
        width: 100%;
        height: 6px;
        background: var(--border);
        border-radius: 3px;
        overflow: hidden;
        margin-bottom: 12px;
    }
    .progress-bar {
        height: 100%;
        width: 0%;
        background: linear-gradient(90deg, var(--lab-blue), var(--annotation-green));
        border-radius: 3px;
        transition: width 0.1s linear;
    }
    .progress-label {
        font-family: var(--mono);
        font-size: 12px;
        color: var(--text-muted);
        letter-spacing: 0.5px;
    }

    /* =========================================
       MAIN PAPER — VIEWPORT LOCKED
       ========================================= */
    .paper {
        position: relative;
        z-index: 1;
        height: 100dvh;
        overflow: hidden;
        display: flex;
        flex-direction: column;
        justify-content: center;
        align-items: center;
        opacity: 0;
        transition: opacity 0.5s ease 0.2s;
        background: var(--lab-white);
        padding: 2rem;
    }
    .paper.visible { opacity: 1; }

    /* =========================================
       NARRATIVE CONTENT
       ========================================= */
    .lab-narrative {
        max-width: 640px;
        width: 100%;
    }

    .lab-narrative .paper-title {
        font-family: var(--serif);
        font-size: clamp(18px, 3vw, 26px);
        font-weight: 700;
        line-height: 1.3;
        color: var(--text-primary);
        margin-bottom: 6px;
        letter-spacing: 0.5px;
    }

    .paper-meta {
        font-family: var(--mono);
        font-size: 12px;
        color: var(--text-muted);
        margin-bottom: 24px;
        padding-bottom: 16px;
        border-bottom: 2px solid var(--lab-blue);
    }

    .paper-section {
        margin-bottom: 16px;
    }

    .paper-section h2 {
        font-family: var(--sans);
        font-size: 11px;
        font-weight: 600;
        text-transform: uppercase;
        letter-spacing: 2px;
        color: var(--lab-blue);
        margin-bottom: 6px;
    }

    .paper-section p {
        font-family: var(--serif);
        font-size: 14px;
        line-height: 1.7;
        color: var(--text-secondary);
        text-align: justify;
        hyphens: auto;
    }

    .correspondence {
        font-family: var(--mono);
        font-size: 11px;
        color: var(--text-muted);
        margin-top: 20px;
        padding-top: 14px;
        border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
        letter-spacing: 0.5px;
    }

    .correspondence a {
        color: var(--lab-blue);
    }

    /* =========================================
       RESPONSIVE -- TABLET
       ========================================= */
    @media (max-width: 1024px) {
        .paper { padding: 1.5rem; }
        .lab-narrative .paper-title { font-size: clamp(17px, 2.8vw, 24px); }
        .paper-section p { font-size: 13px; }
    }

    /* =========================================
       RESPONSIVE -- PHONE
       ========================================= */
    @media (max-width: 600px) {
        .paper { padding: 1.25rem; }
        .lab-narrative { max-width: 100%; }
        .lab-narrative .paper-title { font-size: 17px; }
        .paper-meta { font-size: 11px; margin-bottom: 18px; padding-bottom: 12px; }
        .paper-section { margin-bottom: 12px; }
        .paper-section h2 { font-size: 10px; letter-spacing: 1.5px; margin-bottom: 4px; }
        .paper-section p { font-size: 13px; line-height: 1.6; text-align: left; }
        .correspondence { font-size: 10px; margin-top: 14px; padding-top: 10px; }
        .journal-badge { font-size: 9px; letter-spacing: 2px; padding: 4px 12px; }
    }

    /* =========================================
       RESPONSIVE -- SMALL PHONE
       ========================================= */
    @media (max-width: 380px) {
        .paper { padding: 1rem; }
        .lab-narrative .paper-title { font-size: 15px; }
        .paper-section p { font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.55; }
        .paper-meta { font-size: 10px; }
    }

    /* =========================================
       PRINT STYLES
       ========================================= */
    @media print {
        .grid-overlay, .intro { display: none !important; }
        .paper { opacity: 1 !important; height: auto; overflow: visible; }
        body { overflow: visible; height: auto; }
    }
</style>

<script>
    /* =============================================
       INTRO SEQUENCE
       ============================================= */
    const introEl = document.getElementById('intro')!;
    const paperEl = document.getElementById('paper')!;
    const progressBar = document.getElementById('progressBar')!;
    const progressLabel = document.getElementById('progressLabel')!;

    function skipIntro() {
        introEl.classList.add('done');
        setTimeout(() => {
            introEl.style.display = 'none';
            paperEl.classList.add('visible');
        }, 400);
    }

    async function runIntro() {
        if (sessionStorage.getItem('laboratory-intro-seen')) {
            skipIntro();
            return;
        }

        const stages = [
            { pct: 15, label: 'Peer Review Status: Formatting check...' },
            { pct: 30, label: 'Peer Review Status: Reviewer 1 assigned...' },
            { pct: 50, label: 'Peer Review Status: Reviewer 2 assigned...' },
            { pct: 65, label: 'Peer Review Status: Minor revisions requested...' },
            { pct: 80, label: 'Peer Review Status: Revisions submitted...' },
            { pct: 92, label: 'Peer Review Status: Final review...' },
            { pct: 100, label: 'Peer Review Status: Accepted' },
        ];

        for (const stage of stages) {
            progressBar.style.width = stage.pct + '%';
            progressLabel.textContent = stage.label;
            await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 300 + Math.random() * 200));
        }

        await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 600));
        sessionStorage.setItem('laboratory-intro-seen', '1');
        skipIntro();
    }

    // Click/key to skip
    introEl.addEventListener('click', () => {
        sessionStorage.setItem('laboratory-intro-seen', '1');
        skipIntro();
    });
    document.addEventListener('keydown', (e) => {
        if (!introEl.classList.contains('done') && (e.key === 'Escape' || e.key === ' ' || e.key === 'Enter')) {
            sessionStorage.setItem('laboratory-intro-seen', '1');
            skipIntro();
        }
    });

    runIntro();
</script>
